#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""skill-evals -- deterministic eval fixtures + checks for Edwin's skills.

Skills are graded today by honor-system self-checks inside their own prompts.
This tool is the mechanical layer: per-skill suites of deterministic boolean
checks that run against the skill's ACTUAL outputs (artifacts + Completion
Reports), plus frozen input fixtures for offline replay (the prerequisite for
GEPA-style optimization). Companion to tools/librarian retrieval eval -- same
.eval-history.jsonl + regression-ALERT conventions.

Commands:
  check <skill> [--artifact PATH] [--report PATH] [--path-override OLD=NEW]
      Run the skill's suite (suites/<skill>.json) against its latest (or
      given) artifact + completion report. Exit 2 on any FAIL.
  check-all
      Default suite for every skill in docs/SKILLS.md + full suites where
      they exist. Summary table. Exit 2 on any FAIL (Plombery non-ok
      signaling, matching budget-watch's pattern).
  fixtures freeze <skill>
      Snapshot the skill's input surface (the "inputs" globs in its suite)
      into fixtures/<skill>/<date>/ with a manifest. 50MB cap per skill;
      newest-N sampling per glob; sampled-vs-full recorded in the manifest.
  list
      Show the check registry and which suites exist.

Completion reports: the runner looks for the newest file under
data/skill-evals/reports/<skill>/ (the orchestrator may save the report text
there after a run). If none exists, report-target checks SKIP -- they never
fail on absence of a captured report.

History: every check/check-all run appends to .eval-history.jsonl.
Regression rule (matches tools/librarian/lib/retrieval_eval.py): a
previously-passing check that fails 2 consecutive runs raises an ALERT line
(ALERTs also exit 2).

Stdlib only. Runs under any python3.
"""

